Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["LLM Scalability and Spin-Glass Transition", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"45529276-98b7-4b04-b1b0-39c02b8f0c8a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Sequence Accuracy Rate", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"3bff0ca1-91b1-483d-ac87-38d51f952227"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Motivation", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"46b5db36-1aa8-48e1-aea9-15b0f7361b80"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Accuracy rate",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " is among the most fundamental and widely adopted evaluation metrics in \
machine learning, especially for classification and other discriminative \
tasks. Its appeal lies in the clarity of its definition: each input has a \
well-defined ground-truth label, and the model\[CloseCurlyQuote]s prediction \
can be judged unambiguously as correct or incorrect. This binary criterion \
makes accuracy a natural measure of performance, enabling direct comparison \
across models and datasets."
}], "TextIndent",ExpressionUUID->"64c11426-1971-4c00-8a9c-dba2b11f1544"],

Cell["\<\
However, this paradigm does not directly extend to large language models \
(LLMs). Many LLM applications\[LongDash]such as machine translation, \
summarization, or dialogue\[LongDash]are inherently sequence-to-sequence \
generation problems. In these settings, the model generates text \
probabilistically, token by token, sampling from a distribution of plausible \
continuations. Crucially, there is rarely a single \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]correct\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] output: multiple valid \
translations, summaries, or conversational responses may exist. Consequently, \
simple exact-match accuracy is insufficient for evaluation, and researchers \
rely instead on a suite of task-specific metrics (e.g., BLEU, ROUGE, \
perplexity, or human judgment) that capture fluency, coherence, and relevance.\
\>", "TextIndent",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.968172681339538*^9, 
  3.968172681639988*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cac605a7-8964-4fc6-878e-\
0e0ea9d1a275"],

Cell["\<\
Yet this limitation is context-dependent. In scientific \
domains\[LongDash]including mathematics, physics, and computer science\
\[LongDash]the nature of the task often changes. Here, many problems admit a \
unique correct solution: a definite numerical value, a closed-form \
expression, or a precise code output. For instance, the question \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]what is 2342342 + 3442342\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] has \
only one acceptable answer, and the model\[CloseCurlyQuote]s response must \
exactly match the correct sequence of digits to be considered correct. In \
such applications, the probabilistic flexibility of LLMs does not diminish \
the importance of exact correctness. The evaluation once again reduces to a \
binary criterion: either the model outputs the correct sequence or it does \
not.\
\>", "TextIndent",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.968172685455654*^9, 
  3.968172686679434*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"95dd3955-d9ff-410e-a230-\
0b009bec254f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This observation motivates the introduction of a new evaluation concept \
tailored for LLMs in scientific applications: the ",
 StyleBox["Sequence Accuracy Rate (SAR)",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". SAR measures the proportion of problem instances for which the LLM \
produces the exact correct sequence as output. By aligning the evaluation of \
LLMs with the well-established standard of accuracy in classification, SAR \
provides a rigorous and interpretable metric for assessing LLMs in domains \
where precision and correctness are paramount."
}], "TextIndent",ExpressionUUID->"9b404a44-1823-4ecb-a731-b263ef352e30"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Definition", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"366e9ecc-9324-4d06-9162-caabaf86394b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalD]", "=", 
    SubsuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["x",
          FontWeight->"Bold"], 
         RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]], ",", 
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["y",
          FontWeight->"Bold"], 
         RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]]}], ")"}], "}"}], 
     RowBox[{"k", "=", "1"}], "K"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "79954030-f862-4f26-a6cb-68c472e5e0f2"],
 " be a ",
 StyleBox["dataset",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " consists of pairs of sequences, where each input sequence ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["x",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], 
    RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "55c03e9a-9393-4771-b64c-d858b9120f64"],
 " is ",
 StyleBox["deterministically",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " mapped to a ",
 StyleBox["unique",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " correct output sequence ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["y",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], 
    RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "eaeafed4-4c4b-45aa-a1d3-c23577533467"],
 ". An LLM trained on the dataset defines a conditional probability \
distribution ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["p", "\[Theta]"], "(", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["y",
      FontWeight->"Bold"], "|", 
     StyleBox["x",
      FontWeight->"Bold"]}], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "8c32d932-bd46-4a09-bef6-1206e430ee85"],
 " over output sequences."
}], "TextIndent",ExpressionUUID->"fb80a353-9fe8-46c9-8563-5e334512ceb4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Definition:", "TextConcreteNoIndent"],
 " The ",
 StyleBox["Sequence Accuracy Rate (SAR)",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " is defined as the geometric mean of the model\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
probability on correct sequences:"
}], "TextNoIndent",ExpressionUUID->"334a6e10-2ed4-4273-9aa0-fdbfb9062f17"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"SAR", "(", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["p", "\[Theta]"], ";", "\[ScriptCapitalD]"}], ")"}], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"exp", "(", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", "K"], 
      RowBox[{
       UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
        RowBox[{"k", "=", "1"}], "K"], 
       RowBox[{"log", " ", 
        RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox["p", "\[Theta]"], "(", 
         RowBox[{
          SubscriptBox[
           StyleBox["y",
            FontWeight->"Bold"], 
           RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]], "|", 
          SubscriptBox[
           StyleBox["x",
            FontWeight->"Bold"], 
           RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]]}], ")"}]}]}]}], ")"}], "."}]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaFramed",ExpressionUUID->"ef8023f4-b171-\
4ea0-9d7a-11591151931d"],

Cell["Remarks:", "TextNoIndent",ExpressionUUID->"03b2d5b0-ac42-476f-9a3b-18ee28aa3ccc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"SAR", "\[Element]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}]}]}], "]"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "b73e11f4-f134-438b-b4d4-ed6884dace57"],
 "; it equals to 1 iff ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[ForAll]", 
     RowBox[{"k", ":", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["p", "\[Theta]"], "(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["y",
          FontWeight->"Bold"], 
         RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]], "|", 
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["x",
          FontWeight->"Bold"], 
         RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]]}], ")"}]}]}], "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],
  
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "ba27dc8c-0b89-402c-b0c2-aa3209ff5669"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"56147760-afcc-4bc6-8186-236c0c50a9f2"],

Cell["\<\
SAR can serve as a learning objective. Maximizing SAR is equivalent to \
minimizing the sequence-level cross entropy.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3e48cc4b-2dc7-46c9-8679-904c11269c26"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "(",
 StyleBox["Optional length normalization",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ") If sequence ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["y",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], 
    RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "49cb1175-55a0-4037-b982-7f89461db57a"],
 " are all of the same length ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "58ea64c9-493d-44c9-bddf-78ee4e7865c8"],
 ","
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a8670fc5-b9c4-4ba8-95ba-40f03b078078"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["SAR", 
     RowBox[{"1", "/", "N"}]], "=", 
    SuperscriptBox["PPL", 
     RowBox[{"-", "1"}]]}], ","}], TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",\
ExpressionUUID->"66f4b1cb-3732-4f1f-97fa-2d4214a26d14"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "links SAR to token-level ",
 StyleBox["perplexity",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (PPL)."
}], "ItemParagraph",ExpressionUUID->"99f9e532-106e-4604-bde1-315aee305712"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Observation", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"387ac68c-c751-4b3d-8849-44bf55e96f9e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In our experiments, we observed that the ",
 StyleBox["Sequence Accuracy Rate (SAR)",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " exhibits a strong dependence on the output sequence length ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "3a008f7e-0805-4aca-8ef3-6596d7b61af0"],
 ". A naive expectation might suggest an exponential decay: since the \
probability of reproducing every token correctly diminishes multiplicatively \
with length, one would anticipate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"SAR", "\[Tilde]", 
    SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[Alpha]"}], " ", "N"}]]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "f9dc764d-363f-4b1b-bc1b-485c2bb6d3db"],
 " for some rate \[Alpha]. However, our empirical results deviate \
significantly from this simple picture. Instead of a smooth exponential \
decay, SAR displays a distinct crossover behavior: it remains relatively high \
for short sequences, then undergoes a rapid drop at a characteristic length \
scale ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["N", "crs"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "b0493f98-b322-40f1-9f65-2f13209fe764"],
 ", with the transition extending over a range ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["N", "rng"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "52bc0d9a-9fb8-4a88-afa1-cc70258f5ab1"],
 "."
}], "TextIndent",ExpressionUUID->"5879204a-6fcb-4eb2-9c21-4fcc151259bf"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This nontrivial scaling suggests that sequence-level accuracy in LLMs is \
not governed solely by ",
 StyleBox["independent token-level errors",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", but is shaped by more complex mechanisms, such as correlations in \
generation, context-length effects, or model calibration at different \
sequence scales. The presence of a well-defined crossover length motivates us \
to investigate the underlying principles that control when and how LLMs \
transition from reliable to unreliable sequence generation, particularly in \
the scientific problem-solving regime where exact correctness is essential."
}], "TextIndent",ExpressionUUID->"8abadb2b-457e-49db-852b-6efd3536a944"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Sherrington-Kirkpatrick (SK) model", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"bc618807-e6d2-4b34-a3bb-f212f63a2c73"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Model Setting", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"2676742d-223d-4d30-9ac9-7d6ab3235712"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To gain insight into the observed crossover behavior of SAR, we propose a \
simplified toy model. Consider an ",
 StyleBox["output sequence",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["y",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["y", "1"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox["y", "2"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", 
      SubscriptBox["y", "N"]}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "fbf5a726-b893-4f49-a117-e24fa67250da"],
 " of length ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "bc8ceb96-c35e-4572-bb9e-3374f593ee12"],
 ". For each token ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["y", "i"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "32a7f43d-8da6-4a43-885e-28338acdfe96"],
 ", we assign an ",
 StyleBox["Ising variable",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["s", "i"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "72125330-629e-478d-bf14-e79215e4b742"],
 ", where"
}], "TextIndent",ExpressionUUID->"9e6b2a85-26e5-4d14-834a-75527831a757"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["s", "i"], "=", 
   TagBox[GridBox[{
      {"\[Piecewise]", GridBox[{
         {
          RowBox[{"+", "1"}], 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{
            SubscriptBox["y", "i"], " ", "is", " ", "correct"}], ","}]},
         {
          RowBox[{"-", "1"}], 
          RowBox[{"otherwise", "."}]}
        },
        AllowedDimensions->{2, Automatic},
        Editable->True,
        GridBoxAlignment->{
         "Columns" -> {{Left}}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, 
          "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}, "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
        GridBoxItemSize->{
         "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, "Rows" -> {{1.}},
           "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
        GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
            Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
             Offset[0.84]}, 
            Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, 
          "Rows" -> {
            Offset[0.2], {
             Offset[0.4]}, 
            Offset[0.2]}, "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
        Selectable->True]}
     },
     GridBoxAlignment->{
      "Columns" -> {{Left}}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}, 
       "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
     GridBoxItemSize->{
      "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, "Rows" -> {{1.}}, 
       "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
     GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
          Offset[0.35]}, 
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, "Rows" -> {
         Offset[0.2], {
          Offset[0.4]}, 
         Offset[0.2]}, "RowsIndexed" -> {}}],
    "Piecewise",
    DeleteWithContents->True,
    Editable->False,
    SelectWithContents->True,
    Selectable->False,
    StripWrapperBoxes->True]}], TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaFramed",Expr\
essionUUID->"fabef648-ee87-4273-a7c6-f2fe77beee4c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "An all-correct out-put sequence corresponds to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["s", "i"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"+", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "5edeaa89-341c-45da-81b3-01ba0cee9538"],
 " for all ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"i", "=", "1"}], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", "N"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "47bd1dc8-a9bf-43e4-ac7c-b534c7982bf7"],
 ", which will be denote as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["s",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], "=", 
    StyleBox["1",
     FontWeight->"Bold"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "62dda30e-ed10-4a42-aab7-62eb5c49615a"],
 " jointly."
}], "TextNoIndent",ExpressionUUID->"f22eca3e-7c2c-4992-911d-f9c34ccb8bd5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If each token were generated ",
 StyleBox["independently",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " with a ",
 StyleBox["token-level accuracy rate",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "tok"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "e32b206b-5b23-4cf5-b45e-828180666561"],
 ", the expected sequence accuracy would scale as"
}], "TextIndent",ExpressionUUID->"539ce7e5-dbb2-4c26-a8c6-3be73c392c6e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"SAR", "=", 
    SubsuperscriptBox["p", "tok", "N"]}], ","}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellTags->
  "xref:132524",ExpressionUUID->"d94a8383-70df-4897-bc5e-a55f2944692a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "which decays ",
 StyleBox["exponentially",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " with sequence length ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "f831f8af-06be-4aa6-8400-37bad11fa687"],
 ". The underlying energy model for the Ising variable is simply"
}], "TextNoIndent",ExpressionUUID->"210bf1aa-6923-47e5-984d-17aa696f653c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"E", "[", 
     StyleBox["s",
      FontWeight->"Bold"], "]"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"-", "h"}], 
     RowBox[{
      UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", "i"], 
      SubscriptBox["s", "i"]}]}]}], ","}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"14649fa6-28d9-\
40b0-9124-df68e3d8fd0e"],

Cell["such that", "TextNoIndent",ExpressionUUID->"da97465a-f12e-407d-bfa9-52717fd74622"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"SAR", ":=", 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox[
      SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
       RowBox[{"-", 
        RowBox[{"E", "[", 
         RowBox[{
          StyleBox["s",
           FontWeight->"Bold"], "=", 
          StyleBox["1",
           FontWeight->"Bold"]}], "]"}]}]], 
      RowBox[{
       UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
        RowBox[{"[", 
         StyleBox["s",
          FontWeight->"Bold"], "]"}]], 
       SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
        RowBox[{"-", 
         RowBox[{"E", "[", 
          StyleBox["s",
           FontWeight->"Bold"], "]"}]}]]}]], "=", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       FractionBox["1", 
        RowBox[{"1", "+", 
         SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"-", "2"}], "h"}]]}]], ")"}], "N"]}]}], ","}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"78f0d695-fb4e-\
4cb7-a224-2bf11b5781ec"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "meaning that the ",
 StyleBox["external field",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["h", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "9ba200f6-b1c3-4770-8a1b-2aadb138c731"],
 " parametrize the token-level accuracy rate as"
}], "TextNoIndent",ExpressionUUID->"3a41460a-841a-4dd2-8a0d-1c794e2b15c8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["p", "tok"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["1", 
     RowBox[{"1", "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "2"}], "h"}]]}]], "."}]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellTags->
  "xref:132608",ExpressionUUID->"bc93ceb4-a7f1-4d90-b736-2128bc1c0080"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "However, this prediction Eq.\[NonBreakingSpace](",
 
 CounterBox["DisplayFormulaNumbered", "xref:132524"],
 ") ",
 "fails",
 " capture the crossover behavior observed in experiments."
}], "TextNoIndent",ExpressionUUID->"62407513-3cce-42aa-8c14-3643af599f2b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Model Hamiltonian", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"83c044df-0487-4ac7-be3a-7ae43e77a743"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We hypothesize that the deviation arises from ",
 StyleBox["all-to-all correlations",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " among tokens during sequence generation. The self-attention mechanism in \
LLMs inherently couples every token to every other token, introducing \
dependencies beyond the independent-token picture. These correlations are not \
purely constructive: noise, interference, or internal competition within the \
network can generate effective ",
 StyleBox["random",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " coupling strengths ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["J", 
    RowBox[{"i", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "j"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "6f08e958-7991-4541-9b86-18b620921ca7"],
 " between the Ising variables ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["s", "i"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "e0bbce8a-84ea-4d80-8181-9a25052130d0"],
 " (the token correctness label). Such couplings modify the collective \
statistics of sequence correctness, producing a non-exponential decay and the \
observed crossover in SAR."
}], "TextIndent",ExpressionUUID->"3e71c845-1474-4787-9245-92d9b8a4d802"],

Cell["We propose the following energy model", "TextIndent",ExpressionUUID->"c1094b88-ef73-4697-9c67-453b3803d5c6"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["E", "J"], "[", 
    StyleBox["s",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], "]"}], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", 
     RowBox[{
      UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
       RowBox[{"i", "<", "j"}]], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["J", 
        RowBox[{"i", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "j"}]], 
       SubscriptBox["s", "i"], 
       SubscriptBox["s", "j"]}]}]}], "-", 
    RowBox[{"h", 
     RowBox[{
      UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", "i"], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["s", "i"], "."}]}]}]}]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaFramed",
 CellTags->
  "xref:132672",ExpressionUUID->"aa878cbb-631c-46b2-b533-40b6d3ac3967"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["s", "i"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "bb5404fa-6d08-4085-98e7-5208b5a10ada"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"i", "=", "1"}], ",", "2", ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", "N"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "d8d54352-95fa-4062-b12b-2f270f53a160"],
 " are ",
